    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Bromley | Kent</placeName>
                    <date>March 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
    
<p>Will you be so good as to send me a line by return of Post, informing me (if you can find out) how many copies of our <hi rend="underline">Proceedings</hi> are annually <hi rend="underline">sold.</hi> I am particularly anxious to know this soon—<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Believe me | Yours very faithfully | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD served as a vice-president of the Geological Society in 1843 (see <hi rend="italic">Proceedings of the Geological Society</hi> 4 (1842–5): 64). His reason for requesting the number of copies of <hi rend="italic">Proceedings</hi> sold is not known. The Annual Report of 1843 lists £18 realised from the sale, but the number of copies is not specified.</note>
        </div>        
            
